    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-03T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="97"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 97</seg>
                </opener>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> message files, <gloss target="#t_FRC1"
                        >FRC</gloss> 53A278, Paris: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Administrator for Economic Cooperation (</hi>
                    <persName corresp="#p_FWC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foster</hi>
                    </persName>
                    <hi rend="italic">) to the United States Special Representative in Europe (</hi>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KM1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Katz</hi>
                    </persName>
                    <hi rend="italic">), at Paris</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-03T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 3, 1951—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Torep1">Torep</gloss> 2951. Reference—<gloss
                        target="#t_Repto1">Repto</gloss> 1852.<note n="1" xml:id="d97fn1">This
                        telegram requested information about the decision concerning whether or not
                        the <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> Mission in Trieste would continue.
                            (<gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> message files, <gloss
                            target="#t_FRC1">FRC</gloss> 53A278, Paris)</note> Review Trieste
                    question indicates variety of persons with varying degrees of interest have <pb
                        facs="0267" n="225" xml:id="pg_225"/> helped make U.S. position maintenance
                    Trieste Mission quite unclear. This cable attempts set forth current
                        State-<gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> view for consideration and
                    appropriate action <gloss target="#t_OSR1">OSR</gloss>.</p>
                <p>All concerned agree advisability reducing Trieste aid and size Mission; however,
                        <persName corresp="#p_PGW1">Perkins</persName> feels politically important
                    continue <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> representation in Trieste
                    independent of <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>/Rome. Feel desirable accede
                    to <persName corresp="#p_PGW1">Perkins</persName>’ view unless you have strong
                    objection.</p>
                <p>Projected <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> work Trieste will presumably
                    require one fairly high level person for <gloss target="#t_PA1">PA</gloss>’s
                    screening requirements, follow-up Trieste production (especially ships), general
                    review economic situation and supervision remaining counterpart. Because special
                    nature these tasks feel shld continue to be directed by <gloss target="#t_ECA1"
                        >ECA</gloss> appointee with status of <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>
                    Mission Chief.</p>
                <p>Would like emphasize wish to follow your judgment size of supporting staff and
                    extent to which <gloss target="#t_OSR1">OSR</gloss> might provide direct support
                    so as to minimize staff requirements Trieste.</p>
                <p>Our present information <persName corresp="#p_GRE1">Galloway</persName> prepared
                    return unless other assignment available.<note n="2" xml:id="d97fn2">In telegram
                            <gloss target="#t_Repto1">Repto</gloss> 2237 from Paris, May 15,
                            <persName corresp="#p_KM1">Katz</persName> informed the <gloss
                            target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> that he concurred with the Department of
                        State view that it was necessary to maintain the <gloss target="#t_ECA1"
                            >ECA</gloss> Mission in Trieste. (<gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>
                        message files, <gloss target="#t_FRC1">FRC</gloss> 53A278, Paris)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FWC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foster</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
